"reasoning\": \"Substitute the expressions from steps 2 and 3 into h₁.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"h₁\",\n        \"step 2\",\n        \"step 3\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"real.logb 2 y = (3/2) * real.logb 2 3.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Rearranging the equation from step 4 gives (2/3) * real.logb 2 y = real.logb 2 3, hence real.logb 2 y = (3/2) * real.logb 2 3.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 4\",\n        \"algebra\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"y = 3 * sqrt(3), so y^2 = 27.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Since y = real.logb 2 x and real.logb 2 y = (3/2) * real.logb 2 3, exponentiating base 2 yields y = 2^((3/2) log_2 3) = 3^(3/2) = 3 * sqrt(3). Therefore y^2 = 27.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"definition of logarithm\",\n        \"properties of exponents and logarithms\",\n        \"step 5\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"(real.logb 2 x)^2 = 27.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"By definition y = real.logb 2 x, and step 6 shows y^2 = 27.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 6\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": \"27\"\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization."
