    "content": "## Theorem: amc12a_2002_p1\n\nTheorem: amc12a_2002_p1\nGiven: f : ℂ → ℂ\nGiven: h₀ : ∀ x, f x = (2 * x + 3) * (x - 4) + (2 * x + 3) * (x - 6)\nGiven: h₁ : fintype (f ⁻¹' {0})\nProve: ∑ y in (f⁻¹' {0}).to_finset, y = 7 / 2\n\nGoal: ∑ y in (f⁻¹' {0}).to_finset, y = 7 / 2\n\n## English proof (from stage 1)\n{\n  \"key_observation\": \"Factor the given expression as f(x)=(2x+3)(2x-10)=2(2x+3)(x-5), so the zero set consists of the two roots x=-3/2 and x=5, whose sum is 7/2.\",\n  \"plan\": [\n    \"Rewrite f(x) by factoring out the common term (2x+3).\",\n    \"Solve the resulting product equation f(x)=0 by using the zero-product property.\",\n    \"Identify the full preimage of {0} as the two roots {-3/2, 5}.\",\n    \"Compute the sum of the elements of this finite set.\"\n  ],\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"For every complex number x, f(x) = (2*x + 3) * (2*x - 10).\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"By h₀, f(x) = (2x+3)(x-4) + (2x+3)(x-6). Factoring out the common factor (2x+3) gives f(x) = (2x+3)((x-4)+(x-6)) = (2x+3)(2x-10).\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"h₀\",\n        \"distributive law\",\n        \"factorization\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"For every complex number x, f(x) = 0 if and only if x = -3/2 or x = 5.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"From step 1, f(x)=0 is equivalent to (2x+3)(2x-10)=0. Over ℂ, a product is zero exactly when at least one factor is zero, so either 2x+3=0 or 2x-10=0. Solving gives x=-3/2 or x=5.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 1\",\n        \"zero-product property\",\n        \"solving linear equations\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The set f⁻¹' {0} is exactly the finite set {-3/2, 5}.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"By definition, f⁻¹' {0} is the set of all x such that f(x)=0. Step 2 identifies precisely the two solutions, so the preimage is {-3/2, 5}. The finiteness hypothesis h₁ is consistent with this description.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 2\",\n        \"definition of preimage\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"∑ y in (f⁻¹' {0}).to_finset, y = 7/2.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Since the finite set f⁻¹' {0} has exactly the two elements -3/2 and 5, its sum is (-3/2)+5 = 7/2.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 3\",\n        \"sum over a finite set\",\n        \"arithmetic of rational numbers\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": \"7/2\"\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization."
