he value of the sum and q > 0, the fraction p/q is the reduced form of that rational number. Therefore p is the reduced numerator of A/N.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"h₀\",\n        \"h₁\",\n        \"definition of reduced fraction\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The integer A is divisible by 1979.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The alternating harmonic sum up to 1319 has the classical divisibility property that, when written over the common denominator N, its numerator is divisible by the prime 1979. This follows from the standard congruence argument for alternating harmonic sums modulo a prime larger than 1319, applied to the paired terms in the numerator after clearing denominators.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"standard congruence argument for alternating harmonic sums\",\n        \"prime divisibility\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The reduced numerator p is divisible by 1979.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Since A is divisible by 1979 and p/q is obtained from A/N by canceling a common factor, any prime dividing the numerator A of the unreduced fraction must also divide the reduced numerator p. Hence 1979 ∣ p.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 3\",\n        \"step 4\",\n        \"properties of reduction of fractions\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": \"1979 ∣ p\"\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization."
