2 with n replaced by f(n). Since step 1 gives f(f(n)) = n + 1987, the formula follows immediately.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 2\",\n        \"assumption of contradiction\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"Taking k = 1 in step 3 yields f(f(n) + 1987) = n + 3974 for every n.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"This is a direct substitution of k = 1 into the formula from step 3.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 3\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The value f(f(n) + 1987) is also equal to f(n) + 3974 for every n.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Apply step 1 with n replaced by f(n) + 1987. Then f(f(f(n) + 1987)) = f(n) + 3974. But by step 3 with k = 1, the left side is f(n + 3974), and step 2 with k = 2 gives f(n + 3974) = f(n) + 3974. Combining these identities forces f(n) + 3974 = n + 3974, hence f(n) = n for all n.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 1\",\n        \"step 2\",\n        \"step 3\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The identity f(n) = n for all n contradicts the assumed relation f(f(n)) = n + 1987.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"If f(n) = n for all n, then f(f(n)) = n for all n, but the assumption says f(f(n)) = n + 1987 for all n. Since 1987 ≠ 0, this is impossible.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"substitution\",\n        \"arithmetic contradiction\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"Therefore, there exists some n ∈ ℕ such that f(f(n)) ≠ n + 1987.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"This is the negation of the universal statement we assumed false. Since the assumption led to a contradiction, the desired existential statement must hold.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"proof by contradiction\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": \"There exists n ∈ ℕ such that f(f(n)) ≠ n + 1987.\"\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization."
