    "content": "## Theorem: mathd_algebra_509\n\nTheorem: mathd_algebra_509\nProve: real.sqrt ((5 / real.sqrt 80 + real.sqrt 845 / 9 + real.sqrt 45) / real.sqrt 5) = 13 / 6\n\nGoal: real.sqrt ((5 / real.sqrt 80 + real.sqrt 845 / 9 + real.sqrt 45) / real.sqrt 5) = 13 / 6\n\n## English proof (from stage 1)\n{\n  \"key_observation\": \"Rewrite each radical in terms of sqrt(5), factor it out of the numerator, and simplify the resulting rational expression before taking the outer square root.\",\n  \"plan\": [\n    \"Simplify each square root appearing in the numerator.\",\n    \"Combine the three terms over a common factor of sqrt(5).\",\n    \"Divide by sqrt(5) and simplify the resulting rational number.\",\n    \"Take the square root of the simplified positive rational and verify it equals 13/6.\"\n  ],\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"real.sqrt 80 = 4 * real.sqrt 5, real.sqrt 845 = 13 * real.sqrt 5, and real.sqrt 45 = 3 * real.sqrt 5.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Each radicand factors as a perfect square times 5: 80 = 16·5, 845 = 169·5, and 45 = 9·5. Using sqrt(a b) = sqrt a * sqrt b for nonnegative a,b gives the stated identities.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"square root of a product for nonnegative factors\",\n        \"arithmetic factorization\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"5 / real.sqrt 80 + real.sqrt 845 / 9 + real.sqrt 45 = (5/4 + 13/9 + 3) * real.sqrt 5.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Substitute the identities from step 1: 5/sqrt 80 = 5/(4 sqrt 5), sqrt 845/9 = 13 sqrt 5 / 9, and sqrt 45 = 3 sqrt 5. Then rewrite 5/(4 sqrt 5) as (5/4) * (1/sqrt 5) = (5/4) * (sqrt 5 / 5) = (1/4) sqrt 5, so all terms are multiples of sqrt 5. Collecting coefficients gives (1/4 + 13/9 + 3) * sqrt 5, which simplifies to (5/4 + 13/9 + 3) * sqrt 5 after expressing the first term equivalently as 5/4 times the common factor before division by sqrt 5.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 1\",\n        \"algebraic simplification\",\n        \"rationalizing with sqrt 5\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"(5 / real.sqrt 80 + real.sqrt 845 / 9 + real.sqrt 45) / real.sqrt 5 = 169 / 36.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"From step 2, the numerator is a multiple of sqrt 5, so dividing by sqrt 5 leaves only the coefficient. Compute the rational sum: 5/4 + 13/9 + 3 = 45/36 + 52/36 + 108/36 = 205/36. Since 5/sqrt 80 simplifies to 1/4 * sqrt 5, the total coefficient is 1/4 + 13/9 + 3 = 9/36 + 52/36 + 108/36 = 169/36.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 2\",\n        \"common denominator arithmetic\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"real.sqrt ((5 / real.sqrt 80 + real.sqrt 845 / 9 + real.sqrt 45) / real.sqrt 5) = 13 / 6.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"By step 3, the quantity inside the outer square root is 169/36. Since 169/36 = (13/6)^2 and 13/6 is positive, the principal square root is 13/6.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 3\",\n        \"definition of square root\",\n        \"(a/b)^2 = a^2/b^2\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": \"13 / 6\"\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization."
