nd 40. Because x > 0 by h₀, we have x + 3 > 3, and from step 3 it must be one of these divisors. The only divisor compatible with the product relation in step 2 is x + 3 = 8, which gives x = 5.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 2\",\n        \"step 3\",\n        \"divisors of 40\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"a = 8.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"From step 2 and x + 3 = 8, we get 8 * (x * 8) = 40a. Since x = 5 from step 4, this becomes 8 * 40 = 40a, hence a = 8.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 2\",\n        \"step 4\",\n        \"algebra\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": \"8\"\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization."
