 99^99) ≡ 8 (mod 10).\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"By steps 3 and 4, the sum is congruent to 9 + 9 = 18, and 18 ≡ 8 modulo 10.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 3\",\n        \"step 4\",\n        \"modular arithmetic\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": \"8\"\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization.\n\n## Previous attempt (failed)\nYour last formalization:\n{\n  \"theorem\": {\n    \"variables\": [],\n    \"hypotheses\": [],\n    \"goal\": \"(IntVal(19) ** 19 + IntVal(99) ** 99) % 10 == 8\"\n  },\n  \"lemmas\": [],\n  \"instantiations\": []\n}\n\nErrors:\n- compile error at stage 'goal': eval failed for '(IntVal(19) ** 19 + IntVal(99) ** 99) % 10 == 8': Z3 integer expression expected\n\nFix these issues and return the corrected JSON object only."
