    "content": "## Theorem: mathd_numbertheory_405\n\nTheorem: mathd_numbertheory_405\nVariables: a, b, c (integer)\nGiven: t : ℕ → ℕ\nGiven: h₀ : t 0 = 0\nGiven: h₁ : t 1 = 1\nGiven: h₂ : ∀ n > 1, t n = t (n - 2) + t (n - 1)\nGiven: h₃ : a ≡ 5 [MOD 16]\nGiven: h₄ : b ≡ 10 [MOD 16]\nGiven: h₅ : c ≡ 15 [MOD 16]\nProve: (t a + t b + t c) % 7 = 5\n\nGoal: (t a + t b + t c) % 7 = 5\n\n## English proof (from stage 1)\n{\n  \"key_observation\": \"The recurrence defines the Fibonacci sequence, and Fibonacci numbers modulo 7 have period 16, so it is enough to compute the values at indices congruent to 5, 10, and 15 modulo 16.\",\n  \"plan\": [\n    \"Show that t n is the Fibonacci sequence with t 0 = 0 and t 1 = 1.\",\n    \"Compute the Fibonacci values modulo 7 for indices 0 through 15.\",\n    \"Use the congruences a ≡ 5, b ≡ 10, c ≡ 15 mod 16 and the period-16 property to replace t a, t b, t c by t 5, t 10, t 15 modulo 7.\",\n    \"Add the three residues and reduce modulo 7.\"\n  ],\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"For every natural number n, t n is the nth Fibonacci number defined by F 0 = 0, F 1 = 1, and F n = F (n - 2) + F (n - 1) for n > 1.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The hypotheses h₀, h₁, and h₂ exactly match the defining initial conditions and recurrence for the Fibonacci sequence. Therefore t agrees with the Fibonacci sequence by induction on n.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"h₀\",\n        \"h₁\",\n        \"h₂\",\n        \"induction on n\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The values of t n modulo 7 for n = 0,1,2,...,15 are 0,1,1,2,3,5,1,6,0,6,6,5,4,2,6,1.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Starting from t 0 = 0 and t 1 = 1, repeatedly applying the recurrence gives the Fibonacci sequence. Reducing each term modulo 7 yields the listed residues.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 1\",\n        \"modular arithmetic\",\n        \"recurrence computation\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"t (n + 16) ≡ t n [MOD 7] for every natural number n.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"From step 2, the residues modulo 7 repeat after 16 terms: the block from 0 to 15 is followed by the same starting residues again. This establishes period 16 modulo 7 for the sequence t.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 2\",\n        \"periodicity of Fibonacci modulo 7\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"t a ≡ t 5 [MOD 7], t b ≡ t 10 [MOD 7], and t c ≡ t 15 [MOD 7].\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The congruences h₃, h₄, and h₅ say that a ≡ 5, b ≡ 10, and c ≡ 15 modulo 16. By step 3, changing the index by a multiple of 16 does not change the value modulo 7, so the corresponding t-values are congruent modulo 7.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"h₃\",\n        \"h₄\",\n        \"h₅\",\n        \"step 3\",\n        \"congruence compatibility\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"(t a + t b + t c) % 7 = 5.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"By step 4, the sum is congruent modulo 7 to t 5 + t 10 + t 15. From step 2, these are 5, 6, and 1 modulo 7, so their sum is 12 ≡ 5 mod 7. Hence the remainder upon division by 7 is 5.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 2\",\n        \"step 4\",\n        \"modular addition\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": \"5\"\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization."
